				\begin{document}$$I_{PL}^{FB} = C\sqrt {E - E_{g} (T) + E_{A} } \exp \left(\frac{{ - (E - E_{g} (T) + E_{A} )}}{kT} \right)$$\end{document}here, C is a constant, Eg(T) is given by Eq. (9), k is the Boltzmann constant, and EA is the activation energy of an impurity state. Equation (1) only works well in describing the FB lineshape for the max peak and the higher energy tail. The low energy sub-band gap tail would require a treatment similar to Katahara’s treatment of the band-to-band emission and we simply used the actual tail data to fully reconstruct the FB emission curves. With the two separate PL lineshapes fully resolved, we integrated the area under the FB curve to obtain the total photon flux and plotted it as a function of T in Fig. 7. We also plot the max peak energy as a function of temperature in Fig. 7 (right y axis).Figure 6
